    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS - WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTMENT - REAR
        AXLE JAM NUT INSTALLATION (DOUBLE NUT)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>REAR AXLE JAM NUT INSTALLATION (DOUBLE NUT)</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400112">Figure 12</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400113">Figure 13</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400114">Figure 14</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400115">Figure 15</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After wheel hub, bearings, and adjusting nut are installed, rotate the wheel and hub
                assembly while tightening the adjusting nut to 50 ft-lbs. (68 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Back off inner adjusting nut 1/4 turn.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the locking washer.</para>
            <para>With a doweled adjusting nut, install lockwasher. If lockwasher does not fit dowel, back off adjuster
                nut to the nearest hole in the lockwasher.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400112" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400112" filename="../figg14/g1400112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Rear Axle Jam Nut Installation - Bend Lockwasher Type</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCKING WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. ADJUSTING NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1400113" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400113" filename="../figg14/g1400113.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Rear Axle Jam Nut Installation - Doweled Adjusting Nut Type</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. JAM NUT LOCKING WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PIERCED LOCK RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ADJUSTING NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten jam as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lock nut up to and including 3 1/4 inches (82.55 mm) with bend type lockwasher. Tighten
                    the jam nut to 250 - 275 ft-lbs. (339 - 373 N&#8226;m). After the jam nut is tightened, bend one tab
                    over the jam nut.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Doweled adjusting nut 3 3/8 inches (85.73 mm) and larger with pierced lockwasher.
                    Tighten the jam nut to 350 - 375 ft-lbs. (475 - 508 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check
                    <hotlnk document="s14001t_7.xml" xrefid="hl1400105">bearing end play
                        <xref refid="hl1400105"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1400114" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400114" filename="../figg14/g1400114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 14. Adjusting Nut Identification and Installation - Dowel-Type Spindle Nut Washer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTING NUT (INNER)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DOWEL PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SPINDLE WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. OUTER NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1400115" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400115" filename="../figg14/g1400115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Adjusting Nut Identification and Installation - Tang-Type Spindle Nut Washer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BEND TANGS PERPENDICULAR TO CLOSEST FLAT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTING NUT (INNER)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OUTER NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. NUT LOCK</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
